<p>Appleâ€™s removal of ICEBlock from the App Store is, in multiple ways, <em>worse</em> than Appleâ€™s removal of HKmap.live from the App Store back in 2019. First, you cannot take a disagreement with the Chinese government to court. Here in the United States, you can. But Apple chose not to. Thatâ€™s a display of weakness. </p>

